${bullet}Various code cleanup. Now 16-bit clean, among other things. :-)
${ulend}
${h3}0.33 - 2000/02/21:${h3end}

New features:${pul}

${bullet}Support for encoding and decoding Quoted-Printable headers and bodies,
${indent}primarily in SOUP packets. Decoding is always performed; encoding is
${indent}performed subject to the new .mmailrc keywords \"outCharSet\", \"UseQPHead\",
${indent}\"UseQPMailHead\", \"UseQPNewsHead\", \"UseQPMail\" and \"UseQPNews\". Thanks to
${indent}Peter Karlsson for some of the code.

${bullet}Support for the OPX format has been removed. I hope this will be only
${indent}temporary. The reason is not technical. If you're affected by this, and
${indent}you'd like to continue using OPX, please email me privately.

${bullet}Support for individual packet types may now be disabled when compiling, in
${indent}order to save a little space in the executable. The packet modules to
${indent}include are selected in the \"modules\" file.

${bullet}The Rename function in the packet list now brings up a Blue Wave-style
${indent}default filename, with a numeric extension based on the last one found
${indent}plus one, unless the packet already has a numeric extension. Also, rename
${indent}failures are reported, and you can no longer rename to the name of an
${indent}existing file.

${bullet}Some extra pop-up notices like \"Opening...\", mainly for the benefit of
${indent}slower systems. :-) There are also additional non-fatal error messages in
${indent}several places, as when a Save fails.

