${bullet}Specifying pathnames that end in a slash or backslash (e.g., in .mmailrc)
${indent}should now work correctly.

${bullet}The extraneous \"bw\" prefix found on many of the .mmailrc variable names
${indent}is no longer needed, though it will still be recognized for backwards
${indent}compatibility.

${bullet}Space bar now works in the little area list.

${bullet}The QWK \"Personal\" area no longer appears in the little area list, nor
${indent}can messages be entered in it from the area list.

${bullet}Unrecognized packets no longer cause a segfault (just an exit).

${bullet}Added trivial SIGWINCH handlers for AddressBook and TaglineWindow (they
${indent}just exit that menu).

${bullet}Fatal errors are now reported correctly in the OS/2 version, even when
